job_description: $$$ In the next 30 years, the world will transform every part of the built environment to be climate positive green infrastructure. Knowing what, where, and how to build infrastructure like solar farms is one of the great opportunities of our time.\ \ Paces is software for green infrastructure developers to identify the best places to build and manage their projects. Our software supports renewable energy, EV charging, carbon sequestration and data center customers with interconnection, permitting and siting of their projects. We are venture backed from Navitas Capital, Resolute Ventures, Y Combinator, and other top tier VCs.🌳 TL;DRWe are looking fora scrappy and customer centric full-stack engineerto join us as we scale up. $$$ About PhonePe Engineering - USPhonePe is India's leading digital payments App with over 380 Mn users, driving over 3 Bn monthly transactions adding up to $830 Bn in Annual TPV run rate. We have successfully digitized close to 30 million offline merchants, covering 99% PIN codes in the country.We are a homegrown success story and have emerged as India's largest payments app, and the engineers in the bay area can now be a part of our exciting journey. It is also an opportunity to grow one of the largest apps and transaction platforms in India. In fact, there are a handful of companies in the world operating at this scale today.The OpportunityPowering our massive scale is a 650 people strong engineering team in India, which has delivered best in class transaction speed and reliability, and has led to the creation of one of the world's largest payments platforms. For our next phase of our growth, we need to continue delivering superior performance and reliability on our mobile apps, while handling the diverse set of mobile devices and networks in India.This position is for the US Mobile core team at PhonePe. Mobile core is split between the US and India, with a plan to have about 10 engineers at each location. This split will allow the US team to work on self-contained and forward looking problems, with the India team which will interface more directly with the rest of the organization.The team will be responsible for driving the Android and iOS platforms. This will involve everything; build and release, developer tools, code quality, performance and reliability, internal and external SDKs, cross-platform frameworks, application security and incorporating best practices. This will also include exploring new technologies (for e.g. on-device machine learning, offline payments etc).We're looking for people who are interested in mobile platforms, building for scale, and can work independently in a fast-paced environment. And for engineers who are interested in spending time in India, we will fly you to India, and support working from here for upto 3 months a year!Requirements:Anywhere from 1+ years of experience with Android/iOS, with experience or interest in mobile infrastructure (e.g. platform / frameworks / performance)Strong passion for programming in general.Strong problem-solving skills - we face problems at scale that haven't been solved before (or have only been solved by a handful of companies)For senior engineers, strong system design and architecture skillsAbility to work independently with minimal supervision, and ability to unblock yourself.Flexibility around time zone, given the US/India split.Curiosity to tinker around, explore new paradigms and strong zest for continuous improvement.Eligibility Criteria:Valid Green CardValid H1B VISAValid F1 VISABenefits for Full time employees @PhonePe USAInsurance Benefits:- Employees have 100% Employer sponsored comprehensive Insurance plans which cover Medical, Dental, Vision & Life CoverWork Life Balance:-Leave policy: Unlimited paid time off, to rest and get away from everyday routine or attend to personal tasksRetirement Benefits:- 401K: PhonePe will match 50% of employee's contribution up to IRS limit in 401K fundMobility Benefits:-Relocation: Allowance of $7000 is provided during relocationWellbeing Benefits:-Physical wellbeing: Allowance of $1000 is provided annuallyLearning Assistance:-Learning wallet is loaded annually with $7000, which can be claimed in single or multiple instancesClick here forPhonePe Privacy Notice for California PhonePe PersonnelOther Benefits:-Work from India: Up to 2 months a year, subject to tax liabilityCompany will pay for international flight and 15 days of hotel accommodation in Bangalore once per yearEmployees can work from any location for the remaining time in India.Show moreShow less

$$$ We exist for workers and their employers -- who are the backbone of our economy. That is where Centivo comes in -- our mission is to bring affordable, high-quality healthcare to the millions who struggle to pay their healthcare bills.Centivo is looking for aSoftware Engineerto join our team!We are looking for curious, pragmatic and capable frontend engineers who want to see their work drive better outcomes. You will join our Product Engineering team and work on projects to streamline and improve patient care. Our product engineers work closely with product management, design, and other teams to identify problems and build effective solutions, incrementally delivering high-value, easily maintainable web and mobile solutions that are secure and adhere to acceptable quality & performance benchmarks.You will join in building not only our interfaces and experiences but our culture and processes. Your primary focus will be the user experience across various platforms and devices. Additionally, every engineer on the product engineering team has opportunities to span the stack: you can sharpen your skills through close collaboration on mobile, frontend, and backend engineering challenges. Technical problem-solving appeals to you, but you will also create space for your colleagues to demonstrate the same. We all learn and grow to achieve goals that can never fit into a job description.What you'll do:Working under guidance of the Director Technology, you will:Front-end Development:Develop and maintain user interfaces that are responsive, accessible, and cross-browser compatible.Collaborate with UI/UX designers to implement designs and ensure a seamless user experience.Optimize front-end code for performance and scalability.Back-end Development:Design, develop, and maintain server-side logic.Implement and maintain databases using SQL technologies.Develop APIs (Application Programming Interfaces) for communication between the front-end and back-end systems.Ensure security, authentication, and authorization measures are implemented to protect data and resources.Database Management:Design and optimize database schemas to ensure efficient data storage and retrieval.Write database queries and optimize their performance.Ensure data integrity, consistency, and security.Version Control and Collaboration:Use version control systems to manage codebase changes and collaborate with team members.Participate in code reviews to ensure code quality, readability, and maintainability.Work closely with cross-functional teams, including designers, product managers, and quality assurance engineers, to deliver high-quality software.You should have:You have experience with more than one front-end language or framework and have shipped software into production.You set a high bar for technical excellence, and you want to help your peers achieve it.You can anticipate technical risks and can help mitigate them.You are familiar with a variety of approaches to debugging, maintaining, and improving UI/UX systems.You seek simple answers to complicated questions.Strong Typescript and React skillsExcellent oral and written communications; an ability to present information in a way that establishes rapport, persuades others, gains understandingProven organization skills with attention to detail and follow-upAbility to work independently and on a teamAbility to prioritize and handle multiple tasksComfort with ambiguity and working without well-established policies and practicesWhat does success look like?Join the Product Engineering team as a frontend engineer to enhance our UI/UX systems. You will help define UI patterns that balance development needs with user needs for simplicity, accessibility, performance, and monitoring.Help the team refine and maintain engineering processes that contribute to a great user experience — including writing tests and technical documentation.Routinely ship high quality software that helps simplify healthcare for our patients and clinicians.Engage in the entire life cycle of product engineering, including (but not limited to) sprint planning, retrospectives, on-call rotation, and deploying software.Build an understanding of our business, and our unique approach to health care so that your technical decisions impact the course of the company.Work Location:Remote; preference may be given to individuals geographically located within current or anticipated markets.Applicants must be authorized to work for ANY employer in the U.S. We are unable to sponsor or take over sponsorship of an employment Visa at this time.Pay TransparencyThe ranges we place in our job postings reflect what we anticipate to be the minimum to maximum of the base salary for this role. Additionally, our overall benefits package includes a few things you may consider towards a total compensation such as bonus, health benefits (some employer paid), PTO, and equity option grants.Salary Range$106,000—$134,500 USDOur Values:Resilient – This is wicked hard. There is no easy button for healthcare affordability. Luckily, the mission makes it worth it and sustains us when things are tough. Being resilient ensures we don't give up.Uncommon - The status quo stinks so we had to go out and build something better. We know the healthcare system. It isn't working for members, employers, and providers. So we're building it from scratch, from the ground up. Our focus is on making things better for them while also improving clinical results - which is bold and uncommon.Positive – We care about each other. It takes energy to do hard stuff, build something better and to be resilient and unconventional while doing it. Because of that, we make sure we give kudos freely and feedback with care. When our tank gets low, a team member is there to be a source of new energy. We celebrate together. We are supportive, generous, humble, and positive.Who we are:Centivo is an innovative health plan for self-funded employers on a mission to bring affordable, high-quality healthcare to the millions who struggle to pay their healthcare bills. Anchored around a primary care based ACO model, Centivo saves employers 15 to 30 percent compared to traditional insurance carriers. Employees also realize significant savings through our free primary care (including virtual), predictable copay and no-deductible benefit plan design. Centivo works with employers ranging in size from 51 employees to Fortune 500 companies. For more information, visit centivo.com.Headquartered in Buffalo, NY with offices in New York City and Buffalo, Centivo is backed by leading healthcare and technology investors, including a recent round of investment from Morgan Health, a business unit of JPMorgan Chase & Co.Show moreShow less

At Blueprint, you'll have the opportunity to work with multiple clients and teams, such as data science and product development, all while learning, growing, and developing new solutions. We guarantee you won't find a better place to work and thrive than at Blueprint.We are looking for aJr. Software Development Engineerto join us as we build cutting-edge technology solutions! This is your opportunity to be part of a team that is committed to delivering best-in-class service to our customers.In this role you will contribute to the development, deployment, and maintenance of our Azure-based reinforcement learning loop project. The ideal candidate will have experience with Azure deployment, CICD processes, and C#/app development/debugging. They will play a crucial role in packaging components, ensuring compliance, automating processes, and providing documentation for seamless project integration.Responsibilities:Package the reinforcement learning loop component in a Docker image or similar mechanism.Publish the packaged component to a public container registry like Azure Container Registry.Ensure compliance with internal release tracker process and certification for public release.Publish Bicep scripts to create related resources for deploying the image in Azure subscriptions.Open-source the repository for the component following Microsoft's open-source process.Create comprehensive documentation for easy project consumption.Perform system runs, conduct sanity checks, performance tests, and troubleshoot issues.Qualifications:Bachelor's degree in computer science, software engineering, or a relevant field required.Minimum of 2 years of experience in software development and deployment.Verbal and written communication skills, problem-solving skills, customer service, and interpersonal skills.Ability to work independently and manage time effectively.Package C# components, build container images, and automate related processes.Basic troubleshooting skills and the ability to make system changes to resolve issues.Basic knowledge of computer hardware and software.Proficiency in C#, Docker, CI/CD, Azure services (EventHub, Storage, AKS), and Azure deployment tools (Bicep, ARM, identity).Preferred Qualifications:Familiarity with Bicep scripting language.Salary RangePay ranges vary based on multiple factors including, without limitation, skill sets, education, responsibilities, experience, and geographical market. The pay range for this position reflects geographic based ranges for Washington state: $80,000 - $87,000 USD/annually. The salary/wage and job title for this opening will be based on the selected candidate's qualifications and experience and may be outside this range.Equal Opportunity EmployerBlueprint Technologies, LLC is an equal employment opportunity employer. Qualified applicants are considered without regard to race, color, age, disability, sex, gender identity or expression, orientation, veteran/military status, religion, national origin, ancestry, marital, or familial status, genetic information, citizenship, or any other status protected by law.If you need assistance or a reasonable accommodation to complete the application process, please reach out to: recruiting@bpcs.comBlueprint believes in the importance of a healthy and happy team, which is why our comprehensive benefits package includes:Medical, dental, and vision coverageFlexible Spending Account401k programCompetitive PTO offeringsParental LeaveOpportunities for professional growth and developmentLocation:RemoteShow moreShow less
